The paper deals with the problem of phaseless compressive sensing, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of partial support information also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the numerical experiments conducted in the paper may also fall under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
